        <detaileddescription>
<para>Call this before drawing a window. <computeroutput>expectedWindowName</computeroutput> must match the window name. The remaining parameters are forwarded to <computeroutput>ImGui::SetNextWindowPos()</computeroutput>, expect for one time where we find a free rect and use it instead. <computeroutput>cond</computeroutput> must not be <computeroutput>ImGuiCond_Always</computeroutput> (aka 0), in that case we just forward the arguments and don&apos;t try to find a rect. We automatically avoid all windows with <computeroutput>[rect_allocator_ignore]</computeroutput> anywhere after <computeroutput>##</computeroutput> in the name. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
